HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 151
By Jones J
A RESOLUTION to recognize and honor Jane Osgerby of
Nashville on the occasion of her eightieth
birthday.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pay tribute to
those citizens who are celebrating special occasions in their estimable lives; and
WHEREAS, Jane Osgerby celebrated her eightieth birthday on February 4, 2025, a
milestone that was commemorated as yet another precious souvenir of life's rich pageant; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Osgerby's longevity has privileged her to experience firsthand the
breadth and span of American history, and her remarkable actions therein have beautifully
added to the tapestry of our nation's story; and
WHEREAS, Jane Osgerby was born in Tullahoma but has been a resident of Nashville
since 1975; and
WHEREAS, her expansive career has included thirty-five years at the Tennessee Board
of Probation and Parole, alongside a multitude of other jobs, such as being a counselor at the
Tennessee Prison for Women, supervising community service work, and working in the
courtroom of Judge A.A. Birch; and
WHEREAS, a passionate community advocate and lover of music and history, Ms.
Osgerby is a dedicated archivist, who has preserved and documented such movements and
events as the Freedom Rides anniversaries and her own family history; and
WHEREAS, her advocacy work has rendered her a world traveler, from South Africa to
the Delta of Mississippi, and she has intensely studied ways to foster intergenerational
organizing and coalition building to assist with human rights campaigns and nonviolence; and
